## Before/After Toggle — Implementation Detail

1. In `layout_tab._on_ai_placement_completed()`, save the received nodes as `self._placement_snapshot_before_sym = copy.deepcopy(data["nodes_before_symmetry"])` if the pipeline provides a pre-symmetry snapshot, otherwise store current nodes before loading new ones.
2. A toolbar `QAction("↔ Before/After", ...)` toggles `self._showing_before`.
3. The toggle simply swaps which node-list is fed into `_load_from_data_dict`.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The pipeline must expose `nodes_before_symmetry` in its final payload. This requires a one-line change in `placement_worker._finalize_pipeline()` to save the pre-symmetry state (already stored as `deterministic_snapshot` in `LayoutState`).

